    Class Description
    ArrayMapping<E extends KeyableBean,T extends KeyableBean>
    ArrayMappingImpl<E extends KeyableBean,T extends KeyableBean>
    FkMapping implementation. Uses "fluent" style methods to set values.
    BaseMapping<E extends KeyableBean>
    Abstract base class for PropertyMapping.
    FieldMapping<E extends KeyableBean>
    FieldMapping is a PropertyMapping for a property that is not a foreign key or array, for example Person#FirstName.
    FieldMappingImpl<E extends KeyableBean>
    FieldMapping implementation. Uses "fluent" style methods to set values.
    FkMapping<E extends KeyableBean,T extends KeyableBean>
    FkMapping is a PropertyMapping for a property that is a foreign key, for example Contact#PrimaryAddress.
    FkMappingImpl<E extends KeyableBean,T extends KeyableBean>
    FkMapping implementation. Uses "fluent" style methods to set values.
    LinkMapping<E extends KeyableBean,T extends KeyableBean>
    Base interface for FkMapping and ArrayMapping
    MappingConstants
    Various constants used in Contact mapping.
    MappingDirection
    Specifies the direction of a mapping.
    PropertyMapping<E extends KeyableBean>
    A PropertyMapping contains information for mapping between an entity in the Contact graph of a ContactManager client (BC, CC, PC) and XML. Base interface for all mapping classes in this package. This class is parameterized by the type of the entity for the PropertyReference. For example, a PropertyMapping for Address#City would be of type PropertyMapping
